The 5th anniversary of the Safaricom Jazz Lounge was held at Uhuru Gardens on November 4.  It featured renowned performers such as Senegalese Alune Wade, US vocalist Kavita Shah, The Limericks and Mambo Tribe from Kenya.  Music lovers enjoyed a selection of pure jazz, as well as a mix of jazz fusions with influences from around the world. Proceeds from the event went towards supporting Ghetto Classic.  